g.text: 1) Booking for anything is usually a two phase process.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - Phase 1: You add something to the cart & proceed ahead with the booking

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: - Phase 2: There is a timer of 10 minutes or something. During this period the item

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: is reserved for you and if the payment succeeds then booking is made. else item is released.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 2) Database Pick: We require consistency & there is a good relationship between the

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: tables that we have listed hence we go for SQL database.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 3) External Payment Services: So from our booking service we pass the call to

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: some external payment service that further calls bank/credit card services

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: to process the payment and it does this asynchronously. Hence our service subscribes

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: to it via a web hook so that once payment requests is processed we get updated.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: 4) lets say we made the payment but somehow it failed. now in the table the ticket is marked

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: as reserved. It stays reserved indefinitely if we don't intervene. One way is to make a cron job run

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: every ten minutes. The issue with cron job is that the ticket doesn't get released in realtime. Instead

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: we can use a distributed lock.
